description.plain:
Lola Brooke is a rapper and a songwriter, native of Bed Stuy, Brooklyn, New York.

Lola has been writing music since she was eight years old but started her career as an artist at the age of 23.

In 2016 she signed with Team80, a New York City based record label. Lola then dropped her first music video to a freestyle titled “2017 Flow” (released January 1st, 2017) which brought light to the artist’s talent with the motto “Bars is back” felt throughout the freestyle as an anthem.

Lola Brooke has performed at events such as Break The Internet Fest, HOT97’s “Who’s Up Next”. She has featured in Maino’s album The Ghetto God (feat Casanova), Jaquae album Chapter 3 and and has collaborated with Black Youngsta.

Her list of acknowledgments also include features in True Urban Culture Magaizine and The Source Magazine.

She is inspired by artists such as Meek Mill, Lil Wayne, and Foxy Brown.

If you ask her who she sounds like she will simply respond “I sound like me.”
